<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870828-0046 </DOCNO><HL> Financing Business:Bonneville Pacific Corp.</HL><DD> 08/28/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> BPCOSTOCK MARKET, OFFERINGS (STK) </IN><TEXT>   BONNEVILLE PACIFIC CORP. said it sold 2.6 million common shares at $12.50 each. In national over-the-counter trading yesterday, Bonneville Pacific closed at $12.625, down 37.5 cents. Of the total, the company sold 2.1 million shares, and holders the rest, the Salt Lake City-based developer and operator of alternative energy plants said. Proceeds will be used for developing and acquiring more power-production facilities, Bonneville said. The lead underwriter was Drexel Burnham Lambert Inc. </TEXT></DOC>